SLtools is a library designed to support strong lensing applications 

See INSTALL file for installation details.

The library contains the following packages:

    catalog
    coordinate
    gravlens
    image
    io
    lens
    plot
    string

The bin folder has links to standalone modules.

Once the library is installed, you can import their packages. Example:

    import sltools.image

Use the help command to see the available modules or details for this package.

    help(sltools.image)

    help(sltools.image.add_images)

The following command makes the package modules available in the current namespace:

    from sltools.images import *

